HEADWORD: Oft
<hw>Oft</hw> <pr>(⟦ocr⟧ft; 115)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>oft</ets>; akin to OS. & G. <ets>oft</ets>, OHG. <ets>ofto</ets>,
Sw. <ets>ofta</ets>, Dan. <ets>ofte</ets>, Icel. <ets>opt</ets>, Goth.
<ets>ufta</ets>; of uncertain origin. Cf. <er>Often</er>.]</ety>
<def>Often; frequently; not rarely; many times.</def>
<mark>[Poetic]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Oft</qex> she rejects, but never once offends.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
